#: ../../source/faq.rst:377
msgid "SMS notices/messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:379
msgid "**Question**: I want Koha to send notices via SMS, what do I need to do?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:381
msgid "**Answer**: First you need to choose a SMS service to use with Koha. There is a list available here: http://search.cpan.org/search?query=sms%3A%3Asend&mode=all Not all SMS services available to libraries have Perl drivers, so be sure to check this list to see if the provider you're considering is listed. If not you want to ask your provider if they have a Perl module, if not you should consider another service. Some common options in the US (that have Perl drivers) are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:390
msgid "AQL (`www.aql.com <http://www.aql.com>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:392
msgid "Wadja (`wadja.com <http://wadja.com>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:394
msgid "Ipipi (`ipipi.com <http://ipipi.com>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:396
msgid "T-mobile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:398
msgid "SMSDiscount (`smsdiscount.com <http://smsdiscount.com>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:400
msgid "Clickatell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:402
msgid "Alternatively you can configure Koha to send SMS via Email. In order to use this feature you need to set the :ref:`SMSSendDriver` system preference to 'Email' and confiugre the email gateways for the different :ref:`SMS cellular providers <sms-cellular-providers-label>` of your patrons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:407
msgid "In any case you might want to check if sending SMS to your patrons is legal in your location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:410
msgid "**Question**: What about in India?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:412
msgid "**Answer**: India does not yet have too many options here. This is partly due to the Telecom regulatory authority's (TRAI) stipulations about transactional SMSes and limits on the number of SMSes that may be sent/received per users per day. India specific drivers include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:417
msgid "Unicel Technologies Pvt Ltd (`unicel.in <http://unicel.in>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:422
msgid "Email notices/messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:424
msgid "**Question**: How do I prevent my libraries notices ending up marked as spam?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:426
msgid "**Answer**: This is a complicated topic, but thankfully Koha gives you a good degree of control via various system preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:429
msgid "For every email sent out from Koha there are three important addresses for the system to get correct, *From*, *Reply-to* and *Sender*. These are configurable at both the system and library level and should fall back in a suitable manner if any of them are not defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:434
msgid "KohaAdminEmailAddress - This will act as the *From* address and should be an address in the same domain as the koha server [for example noreply@koha-hosting.org]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:436
msgid "ReplytoDefault - This will act as the *Reply-to* address and can be in any domain [for example librarian@mylibrary.com] and this is the address which will be used if/when a patron hits 'Reply' in their email client. Note: This will fall back to KohaAdminEmailAddress when it is not set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:440
msgid "ReturnpathDefault - This will act as the *Sender* address and also needs to be within the koha/email servers domain [for example postmaster@koha-hosting.org] and this is the address which will be used to report if an email bounces for any reason."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:445
msgid "There are parallels to all the above preferences at the per branch level which fall back in the same order as mentioned aboved before falling back to the system level preferences above when required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:449
msgid "If you have the above configured correctly and your emails are still being treated as spam then you likely need to contact your email service provider/dns provider and look into MX, SPF and DKIM records."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:456
msgid "Cataloging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:461
msgid "Authorities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:463
msgid "**Question:** Why can't I edit 1xx, 6xx, or 7xx fields in my catalog record?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:466
msgid "**Answer:** These fields are authority controlled and you probably have the :ref:`BiblioAddsAuthorities` set to \"Don't allow\". When it is set to \"Don't allow\" these fields will be locked and require you to search for an existing authority record to populate the field with. To allow typing in these authority fields set :ref:`BiblioAddsAuthorities` to 'Allow'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:475
msgid "Fields affected by this preference will show a lock symbol in them"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:477
msgid "|image1115|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:479
msgid "**Question:** Can I use Koha without creating authority records?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:481
msgid "**Answer:** If you don't want to create authorities for your records at all, you can remove the authority link by blanking the Thesaurus setting for the fields in your MARC bibliographic frameworks. See also: :ref:`Edit framework subfields <edit-framework-fields-and-subfields-label>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:489
msgid "Koha to MARC mapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:491
msgid "**Question**: What's the relationship between 'Koha to MARC mapping' and 'MARC bibliographic frameworks'?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:494
msgid "**Answer**: Mappings can be defined through 'MARC bibliographic frameworks' OR 'Koha to MARC mapping'. 'Koha to MARC mapping' is just a shortcut to speed up linkage. If you change a mapping in one of these modules, the mapping will change in the other as well. In other words, the two modules 'overwrite' each other in order to prevent conflicts from existing in Koha."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:504
msgid "Number of items per bibliographic record"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:506
msgid "**Question**: Is there a limit on the number of items I can attach to a bib record?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:509
msgid "**Answer**: There is no limit to the number of items you can attach to a bibliographic record. For records with a big number of items exporting the MARC record as ISO 2709 might be problematic as this format has a size limit. Item numbers somewhere between 600 and 1000 items on a 'normal' bibliographic record should be ok."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:518
msgid "Analytics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:520
msgid "**Question**: I am using the :ref:`EasyAnalyticalRecords` feature, but my links in the OPAC and Staff client to 'Show analytics' are not working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:524
msgid "**Answer**: If you plan on using :ref:`EasyAnalyticalRecords` you will want to make sure to set your :ref:`UseControlNumber` preference to \"Don't use,\" this will prevent broken links."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:532
msgid "Acquisitions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:537
msgid "Planning categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:539
msgid "**Question**: What is a planning category?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:541
msgid "**Answer**: When you plan in advance for the way your budget is going to be spent, you initially plan for how it's going to be spent over time, that's the most natural thing to do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:545
msgid "So you plan for $1000 in Jan. $1000 in Feb., $3000 in March, etc. You can basically do the same thing with a list of values in lieu of the months."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:549
msgid "Say you have a list like this one:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:551
msgid "< 1 month"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:553
msgid "< 6 months"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:555
msgid "< 1 year"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:557
msgid "< 3 years"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:559
msgid "< 10 years"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:561
msgid "> 10 years"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:563
msgid "The list is meant to represent when the books acquired were published. Then you plan for it, saying: we want to spend at least 40% of our budgets on books published less than a year ago, 10% on books more than 10 years old, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:568
msgid "Upon acquiring new material, you'll be able to select, for a given item, a value from this list in a drop down. Then, after the material has been acquired, at the end of the year, you'll be able to compare the goals set with what's been achieved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:576
msgid "Serials"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:581
msgid "Advanced patterns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:583
msgid "**Question**: What is the 'inner counter' on the advanced serials pattern interface?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:586
msgid "**Answer**: I think it is better to give an example to understand this :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:588
msgid "Example for a monthly subscription :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:590
msgid "First issue publication date : April 2010"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:592
msgid "Numbering : No {X}, year {Y}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:594
msgid "First issue : No 4, year 2010"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:596
msgid "For the year Y : you will want the year change on January 2011"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:598
msgid "So, the advanced pattern for Y will be :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:600
msgid "Add : 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:602
msgid "Every : 12"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:604
msgid "When more than: 9999999"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:606
msgid "Inner counter: 3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:608
msgid "Set back to: 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:610
msgid "Begins with: 2010"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:612
msgid "Year is going to change after 12 received issues from April 2010, that is in April 2011 if you don't set inner counter. Set inner counter to 3 will say to Koha: change year after 12-3 = 9 received issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:616
msgid "Inner counter says to Koha to take into account the first issues of the year, even if they are not received with Koha. If you begin with first issue of the year write nothing or 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:623
msgid "Reports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:628
msgid "SQL help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:630
msgid "**Question:** I don't know SQL, but I want to write a report that does X. Can you tell me how?"
